 \tan^2 \cfrac{A}{2} + \tan^2 \cfrac{B}{2} + \tan^2 \cfrac{C}{2} \ge 1 
A+B+C = \pi 
\cfrac{A}{2} + \cfrac{B}{2} + \cfrac{C}{2} = \cfrac{\pi}{2} 
\dfrac{A}2, \dfrac{B}2, \dfrac{C}2 \in (0, \pi/2)
f(x) = \tan^2(x)
x \in (0,\pi/2)
f(x)
x_1 = \dfrac{A}2
x_2 = \dfrac{B}2
x_3 = \dfrac{C}2
x_1 + x_2 + x_3 = \dfrac{A+B+C}2 = \dfrac{\pi}2
\dfrac{f(x_1) + f(x_2) + f(x_3)}3 \geq f \left(\dfrac{x_1 + x_2 + x_3}3 \right)
\dfrac{f(A/2) + f(B/2) + f(C/2)}3 \geq f \left(\dfrac{\pi}6 \right)
\dfrac{\tan^2(A/2) + \tan^2(B/2) + \tan^2(C/2)}3 \geq \tan^2(\pi/6) = \dfrac13
\tan^2(A/2) + \tan^2(B/2) + \tan^2(C/2) \geq 1
\cos A= 1- 2 \sin^2(\frac{A}{2})
\sin^2(\frac{A}{2})=1-\cos A
1- \dfrac{b^2+c^2-a^2}{2bc}=\dfrac{2bc-b^2-c^2+a^2}{2bc}
= \dfrac{a^2-(b-c)^2}{2bc}=\dfrac{(a+b-c)(a-b+c)}{2bc}
a+b-c=\dfrac{(s-b)}{2}
a-b+c=\dfrac{(s-c)}{2}
2 \sin^2\dfrac{A}{2}=\dfrac{4(s-b)(s-c)}{2bc}
\sin^2(\dfrac{A}{2})=\dfrac{(s-b)(s-c)}{bc}
